                                        1315,
                                        1032,
                                        2340,
                                        1841
                                    ],
                                    "type": "text",
                                    "content": " studied. For simplicity, we focus our study on the effects of plasma temperature and the role of nuclear plasma interactions (NPIs) on low- energy fusion reactions, with the latter expected to affect stellar nucleosynthesis [11, 12]. Examples of processes involving NPIs are nuclear excitation by electron capture (NEEC) or transition (NEET). These have been observed experimentally but still are not well- understood [13, 14]. The "
                                },
                                {
                                    "bbox": [
                                        1315,
                                        1032,
                                        2340,
                                        1841
                                    ],
                                    "type": "inline_equation",
